(i.e. abuse, neglect) that create these little monsters that are in the public school classrooms.  Two of my best friends are public school teachers, and they won't hesitate when you ask them if you should send your kids to private or public school.....PRIVATE!!! IF you can afford it. Why? Because the govt doesn't pay teachers nearly enough, which makes people NOT want to go into teaching....so there are fewer and fewer good teachers in public schools....and those that are there are getting classrooms that are growing in size with every passing year....and the kids that come from the homes I spoke of above, have behavior issues, learning disabilities, ESL, and...thanks to their parent(s) or lack of..... are just bad kids....SO, teachers have to spend a disproportionate amount of time working with these kids when they really need to be teaching ALL the kids. Yes, the few spoil it for the rest. I want my kid to learn, not to be distracted and somewhat neglected by the system because of those few &quot;needy&quot; ones that ruin it for the normal average kid that wants to learn. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1390" language="en" documentId="2475" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Ronibalony" date="Aug 29, 2013 9:54PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="5" thumbsDown="0" origId="2475" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1390"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>